Precisely.  I've always considered Debuffs to be our "secondary weapon", since we have so many of them.  But for them to be worth filling up my quickbar, they need to have a definate, noticable impact.  A person hit with my Str/Con debuff should really feel it.<P>Personally, I'd like to see our debuffs:<P>Lower swing speed<BR>Lower DPS<BR>Weaken Spell Damage<BR>Decrease movement speed (like a snare)<BR>Lower AF<P>All of those things could potentially be noticable in large fights.  Notice I didn't say "lower HP", because people didn't like being dealt damage that couldn't be healed (although debuffs *can* be healed I think).  <P>And, also, I do as well like the idea of a single-target Mez Bolt.
