Giving us a 55 pet would cause people to whine. Mythic would then nerf our CC to balance out the class. But we're not a pet class, so having a 55 pet isn't an issue. Our other, current abilities should be buffed up.<P>I think debuffs should be like anti-buffs; a high lvl sorcerer's debuffs should be as powerful as a cleric's buffs, only they take away the same amount of stats as cleric buffs would add. 50 enhance gives uber buffs, and 50 mind should give uber debuffs. So if both were used on a person, their stats would remain normal(IE, buffs+debuffs basically=no buffs at all).<P>Pet debuffs aren't really there. You're seeing what happens when a mob becomes a PC - they bite. PCs can beat a mob even con to them because we have armor, stat increases, styles, etc. etc., while pets are at a natural disadvantage.<P>Oh and btw, a quick question. Do pets style? I've seen mobs do it, but never a pet.
</FONT>
